<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to
                                Secretary <persName type="to">Loeb</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lenox,
                                        Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-06"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Following from governor-general Canada: Please personally convey my
                            profoundest and most reverent sympathy to the President on the great
                            personal as well as national loss he has sustained. The sad news has
                            only just reached me on the banks of the Cascapedia.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Durand.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>